        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A pneumoconiosis characterized by granulomatous inflammation that occurs in individuals who develop beryllium sensitization (BeS) a cell-mediated immune response to environmental and occupational beryllium exposure. BeS precedes the lung disease that may present with chronic dry cough fatigue weight loss chest pain and increasing dyspnea."
        },
